<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1410,1748]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1410,1436]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Proepimeron black; scutum black; scutellum black with slightly reddish margins; anepimeron black. Femora brown, the apices broadly yellow; pro- and meso tibiae yellow; hind tibia brown, the base yellow. Wing extensively microtrichose; alula as broad as cell BM. Abdomen black, the 2 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1242,1258,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">nd</superScript>
, 3 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1289,1302,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">rd</superScript>
, 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1335,1348,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">th</superScript>
and 5 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1423,1436,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">th</superScript>
terga with three opaque, velvet-black spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1410,1748]" box="[197,462,1568,1594]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Length. Body 5.0 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
